<HEADLINE>
FT  28 SEP 93 / UK Company News: Greenacre jumps 31%
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By GRAHAM DELLER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
GREENACRE GROUP, the nursing home operator, benefited from continuing
expansion to produce a 31 per cent rise in interim profits, from Pounds
605,000 to Pounds 794,000 pre-tax.
The outcome was achieved despite a turnround from net interest receivable of
Pounds 152,000 to payable of Pounds 45,000.
Over the six months to July 31 the USM-traded group lifted the number of
beds under operation and/or development from 384 to 575, located in 12 homes
across the UK.
Mr Tony Acton, chairman, said the group had 'been little affected by the
occupancy problems experienced by some operators' following the introduction
of Community Care reforms in April.
Turnover rose to Pounds 3.32m (Pounds 2.08m) including a Pounds 194,000
contribution from acquisitions. Profits at the operating level leapt 85 per
cent to Pounds 839,000 (Pounds 453,000) with acquisitions accounting for
Pounds 60,000.
The interim dividend is raised to 0.15p (0.13p), payable from fully diluted
earnings of 0.32p (0.25p) per share.
A strong performance from both existing and new homes was expected in the
second half, Mr Acton said. Panmure Gordon, the group's broker, expects
profits of about Pounds 1.7m and earnings of 0.7p per share for the year to
January 1994.
Shareholders' funds at the period end amounted to Pounds 12.1m (Pounds
11.8m) giving gearing of some 11 per cent (nil).
</TEXT>
