<HEADLINE>
FT  28 SEP 93 / UK Company News: FT-SE Actuaries changes
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE FT-SE Actuaries Industry Classification has agreed the following changes
to constituent companies' classifications, effective from October 1: J
Saville Gordon to Property (FT-A group 69) from Metals and Metal Forming
(8); Sidlaw to Packaging, Paper and Printing (31) from Oil and Gas (51).
In addition, the following companies will be moved to new groups in the
London Share Service on October 1: Aegon to Insurance (Life) from Insurance
(Composite); Berry Birch &amp; Noble to Other Fiancials from Insurance Brokers;
Hawtin to Congolmerates from Textiles; Sleepy Kids to Media from Hotels and
Leisure; West Trust to Food Manufacturers from Textiles.
</TEXT>
