<HEADLINE>
FT  28 SEP 93 / International Company News: Unidare rises to IPounds 2.7m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
UNIDARE, the Dublin-based industrial group, saw an increase in both sales
and pre-tax profits for the the half year to June 30, boosted by its
acquisition of Nasco of the US.
Pre-tax profits were ahead 10 per cent at IPounds 2.68m (Pounds 2.53m)
against IPounds 2.45m.
Turnover was Pounds 63.3m (IPounds 59.9m), including IPounds 9.39m from
acquisitions.
Earnings per share came out ahead at 12.52p (11.71p) and the interim
dividend is 4.4p (4.3p).
