FT  28 SEP 93 / The Lex Column: Hammerson
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The question unanswered by yesterday's interim statement is what terms
Hammerson will offer for enfranchising its restricted voting shares. The
broad hint from the company is that the 10 per cent price differential
between its two classes of shares before May's rights issue will be taken as
evidence of what full voting rights are worth. Ordinary shareholders might
thus expect something like a 1-for-10 bonus issue by way of compensation.
But there is doubtless room for haggling. Since the differential had shrunk
to 8 per cent by yesterday's close, the market may now be anticipating
something less.
