<HEADLINE>
FT  28 SEP 93 / Management (The Growing Business): Consultants get the
thumbs down - In A Nutshell
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Consultants still have a poor image with small business owners despite
schemes such as the government's Enterprise Initiative which attempts to
break down barriers.
A poll* of small firms employing between six and 50 people in and around
Milton Keynes found that most were sceptical of external consultants. They
saw consultants as 'far too expensive', 'not offering practical advice in
layman's terms,' and 'not living in the real world'.
The areas where business owners had most frequently sought help were quality
(44 per cent), sales and marketing (22 per cent), staff and management
development (16 per cent), finance and administration and information
technology (both 13 per cent).
*By Milton Keynes and North Bucks Training and Enterprise Council and Milton
Keynes Business Venture. Tel. 0908 222555.
</TEXT>
