FT  28 SEP 93 / Thatcher picks at Tory wounds
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID OWEN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
STERLING should stay out of the European exchange rate mechanism, Lady
Thatcher, the former prime minister (pictured above with Sir Teddy Taylor),
told Conservative loyalists last night in a speech which threatened to
reopen Tory wounds on Europe just a week before the party's annual
conference, David Owen writes.
