of the shift towards federalism it would bring about. Speaking in the
Southend East constituency of Sir Teddy, the arch Euro-sceptic Tory MP, she
said the British people had their own way of doing things and did not want
to be swamped by Europe.
Tory activists at the Pounds 35-a-head event - which was marked by a huge
police security operation - could not recall her making a single reference
to Mr John Major, the prime minister, or to the current state of the Tory
party.
