<HEADLINE>
FT  28 SEP 93 / Kuwaiti paper warns of pull-out
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JIMMY BURNS and ROGER MATTHEWS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
ONE of Kuwait's leading independent newspapers warned yesterday that the
emirate might be unwilling to invest in the UK if it lost its valuable
sovereign immunity from taxation.
In an editorial, the al-Qabas newspaper reacted strongly to what it called
'the astonishing . . . threats and intimidation about rescinding tax
exemption'.
Last week the FT disclosed that Kuwait may have abused the immunity by
receiving more than Pounds 600m of tax refunds on a Dollars 1.7bn investment
in British Petroleum.
At the weekend Lord Shawcross, one of Kuwait's most distinguished and
long-standing UK advisers, warned of the potential immunity loss in a letter
to a senior member of the emirate's ruling Al-Sabah family.
Yesterday, however, Whitehall officials reacted cautiously to any threat of
investment withdrawal from the UK, pointing out that al-Qabas does not
necessarily reflect Kuwaiti government thinking.
Although the Kuwaiti state sold off some of its UK assets to pay for the
Gulf War, the Kuwaitis still have extensive landholding and other
investments in Britain.
The Foreign Office and the Department and Trade and Industry said yesterday
they had received no approach from the Kuwaiti government expressing concern
on the tax issue.
</TEXT>
