<TEXT>
WHITE-COLLAR town hall workers have voted by 2-1 against taking strike
action in protest at the government's 1.5 per cent pay ceiling, Lisa Wood
writes.
The 500,000 workers are the last big group of workers, apart from the
firefighters, to accept the government's pay ceiling for this year.
Council staff including secretaries, surveyors and social workers had
previously voted to reject the 1.5 per cent.
Mr Dennis Reed, the chief negotiator for Unison, the public sector union,
said most members had voted before the chancellor's fresh warning of a pay
freeze for public sector workers next year.
He said they had been influenced by the fact that most workers had already
settled within the ceiling.
