<HEADLINE>
FT  28 SEP 93 / P&amp;O to shed 450 workers next year
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
P&amp;O European Ferries, the largest UK ferry operator, yesterday announced
plans to shed up to 450 jobs from its workforce of more than 6,000, Charles
Batchelor writes.
The cuts are a response to the prospect of competition from the Channel
tunnel, due to open next year, and new technologies which have reduced the
demand for staff on shore and at sea.
P&amp;O said it expected to dispense with up to 250 jobs on its nine Dover-based
ships and a further 200 shore-based positions at Dover. The company hopes to
achieve the cuts by voluntary redundancies.
P&amp;O said no cuts would occur before next year, but it could not guarantee
there would be no further reductions.
The cuts are expected to fall among ships crews, from officers to ratings
and among reservations and port operations staff. On board ship new
computerised radio equipment has meant vessels no longer need specialist
radio officers.
