<HEADLINE>
FT  27 SEP 93 / People: Non-executive directors
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Plysu, the plastic container manufacturer based at Milton Keynes in
Buckinghamshire, has appointed David O'Shaughnessy as chairman. He replaces
James Summerlin, the group's co-founder.
O'Shaughnessy became a non-executive director of Plysu in July. He is
chairman of Pira International and already holds non-executive directorships
at Barry Wehmiller International and Britton Group. He spent 35 years with
Metal Box where he became a main board director in 1979. He retired from the
board of Carnaud Metal Box in September 1992.
Summerlin, whose retirement was announced at the AGM in July, has been
appointed honorary life president. He remains a non-executive director.
Last year non-executive directors led a boardroom coup against
Richard Gordon, managing director. There was criticism that
Gordon had been unable to delegate following a series of acquisitions by the
group. He was replaced by Malcolm Macintyre, the former manufacturing
director.
