FT  27 SEP 93 / UN sanctions against Unita
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   LUANDA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE United Nations banned the sale of fuel and weapons to the Angolan rebel
movement Unita yesterday in an attempt to force a negotiated end to the
country's bloody civil war, AP reports from Luanda.
The sanctions were an attempt to slow the rebel army which has captured
almost three quarters of Angolan territory. A UN official said: 'We
certainly hope no stronger measures will be necessary to convince Unita that
the time has come for negotiations.'
