FT  27 SEP 93 / UK Company News: Maddox
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Maddox Group, the computer maintenance company, has received 'approaches
which may or may not lead to an offer for all or part of the company'.
Maddox has been told by Lantek Electronic that it is putting C&amp;F into
administrative receivership rather than continuing to fund its losses. In
selling C&amp;F and Seacoast Electric to Lantek in June, Maddox has an
investment in Lantek in loan notes and various preference shares valued in
Maddox's 1992 accounts at Pounds 15.1m, of which Pounds 5.63m related to the
investment in C&amp;F.
