<HEADLINE>
FT  27 SEP 93 / People: Price Waterhouse
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Jermyn Brooks (above) has been elected chairman of Price Waterhouse in
Europe in succession to Sir Geoffrey Bowman, who announced his retirement
earlier this year.
Brooks, 54, was partner in charge of PW in Germany, and is currently joint
managing director of PW in Europe. He has been a member of the PW European
management board since 1989.
As chairman, he will have responsibility for helping shape the future
direction of the firm, though he said yesterday he was still determining his
three or four main priorities.
The PW European organisation was formed through the combination of all the
firm's European operations, including those in the UK, which contribute
about half total fees.
There is some degree of cost- and profit-sharing within the firm's 138
different offices in 28 countries across the continent; revenues were Pounds
775m in the year to June 30.
Brooks joined PW in 1962 and transferred to Frankfurt in 1967 where he
became a partner in 1973. He was in charge of the Iran practice during
1977-79, set up the firm's operations in Turkey in 1981-85, and then led the
audit and management consultancy operations in Germany. He has both English
and German accountancy qualifications.
</TEXT>
