<HEADLINE>
FT  27 SEP 93 / Ticket test case on Gatwick line
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
RAIL TRAVELLERS to and from Gatwick airport will be allowed to transfer
tickets between Gatwick Express and Network SouthEast services, in a test
case for the implications of rail privatisation.
As a first step towards privatisation, from this weekend the London to
Gatwick service is to be split into two separate operations. One management
team, acting as a shadow company, will operate the Victoria-Gatwick express
service, while Network SouthEast will introduce a cheaper fare to attract
customers to its slower services on the same route.
