<HEADLINE>
FT  27 SEP 93 / Cash for company cars 'falls short'
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MOST CASH alternatives to company cars being offered by employers fall 'far
short' of the actual cost to employees of providing their own cars,
according to a study undertaken by Wyatt, the remuneration consultancy and
actuarial group.
The study adds that 'few employees have a clear idea of how to calculate the
true value of a company car in their personal circumstances'.
Based on an annual survey of 260 companies operating sizeable car fleets, it
concludes that these are two of the main reasons why the number of employees
taking up cash offers is low.
1993 Survey of Company Cars and Flexible Benefits Packages, The Wyatt
Company (UK), 21 Tothill Street, London SW1H 9LL. Pounds 75.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>GBZ  United Kingdom, EC.
</CN>
<XX>
Industries:-
