<HEADLINE>
FT  27 SEP 93 / Syria calls for the tightening of 40-year-old Arab economic
boycott against Israel
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   DAMASCUS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Syria called yesterday for the tightening of the 40-year-old Arab economic
boycott against Israel, accusing it of asking for everything in the Middle
East peace process in return for nothing, Reuter reports from Damascus. The
government newspaper Tishreen and state-run Damascus radio said the boycott
could not be abolished before restoration of Arab rights and the recovery of
occupied Arab lands.
</TEXT>
