FT  27 SEP 93 / World Bank/IMF Meeting: Russia suggests creditors write off
part of its foreign debt
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WASHINGTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Russia suggested yesterday that international creditors write off part of
its Dollars 80bn (Pounds 51.9bn) foreign debt but Germany rejected the
request, Mr Theo Waigel, German finance minister, said, Reuter reports from
Washington.
Mr Waigel told reporters that the issue had been raised by Mr Alexander
Shokhin, Russian deputy prime minister. 'But I said we were against this. It
would not find our favour,' Mr Waigel said.
