<HEADLINE>
FT  27 SEP 93 / World News in Brief: Motor racing
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Alain Prost of France won the Formula One world drivers' championship when
he finished second in a Williams behind Michael Schumacher of Germany in a
Benetton in the Portuguese Grand Prix. Briton Damon Hill, also driving a
Williams, finished third.
