FT  27 SEP 93 / World News in Brief: European Monetary System
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Conditions in the exchange rate mechanism were very calm last week because
the D-Mark was under pressure against most currencies as a result of the
crisis in Russia. Only 6.18 percentage points separated the strongest
currency, the Dutch guilder, from the weakest, the Danish krone. Of the
currencies fluctuating in wider bands, the Spanish peseta was the best
performer and was closest to the D-Mark in the grid.
